{{Beauty pageant | photo = | caption = | winner = [[Rose Coyle]] | represented = [[File:Flag of Philadelphia, Pennsylvania.svg|20px]] [[Philadelphia]] | congeniality = | photogenic = | best national costume = | date = September 12, 1936 | venue = [[Steel Pier]], [[Atlantic City]], [[New Jersey]] | presenters = King Neptune | acts = | entrants = 47 | placements = 15 | broadcaster = | debuts = | withdraws = [[Bloomfield]]{{dn|date=July 2011}}, [[Bridgeport, Connecticut|Bridgeport]], [[Bridgeport, Pennsylvania|Bridgeport]], [[Bridgeton]]{{dn|date=July 2011}}, [[Brooklyn]], [[Cleveland]], [[Connecticut]], [[Conshohocken]] | returns = [[Camden, New Jersey|Camden]] }} '''Miss America 1936''', the 10th [[Miss America]] pageant, was held at the [[Steel Pier]] in [[Atlantic City, New Jersey]] on September 12, 1936.<ref>{{cite news|title=Philadelphia Girl is "Miss America"|last=Associated Press|publisher=The LaCrosse (WI) Tribune|page=1|date=1936-09-13}}</ref> Despite winning three of the pageant's contests ("most beautiful girl in evening gown," "most perfect model," and "Miss Outdoors Girl"), Miss Cook County was awarded 3rd runner-up. Miss Connecticut, the 2nd runner-up, won the "Miss Personality" prize, while Miss Philadelphia tap danced her way to the "talent award" as well as winning the coveted crown.<ref>{{cite news|title=Win Beauty Awards|last=Associated Press Wire Photo|publisher=The Lowell (MA) Sun|page=1|date=1936-09-14}}</ref> Entrants from [[Pennsylvania]] took the top honor as well as capturing three other positions in the Top 15.
